      "message": "Please keep it in the same style as other functions here, this module is a candidate for becoming a part of public API and all functions here should look consistent. _regex_list:\n\n1. Should have the same signature as _list(...).\n2. Should have a doc string. Document that it accepts both strings and lists.\n3. Two new lines between functions.\n4. Add a unit test to testdata/misc/validators.star.\n\nAlso the implementation itself is not entirely correct. Each element should be checked to be a string before doing \u0027|\u0027.join(...). Also it is a bit worrisome that regexp_list([\u0027stuff(a\u0027, \u0027b)stuff\u0027]) produces a regexp that accepts \u0027stuffastuff\u0027 etc. Strictly speaking we should validate each individual element is a valid regexp and only then combine them. But I think this can be omitted if _regexp_list documents that is blindly joins strings without validation.",
